The paper discusses privacy-enhancing communication protocols and proposes a formal framework to analyze and compare them with respect to privacy by data minimization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper focuses on identity management systems, which involve the management of personal information, suggesting that it could also belong to the sub-category of "Computers and Society" (cs.CY). The paper also mentions the use of coalitions of actors and a three-layer model of personal information, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of "Databases" (cs.DB). The paper proposes a formal framework for analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) or "Software Engineering" (cs.SE).
